HEADWORD: Archimedes
<hw>Ar`chi*me"des</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct genus of Bryzoa characteristic of
the subcarboniferous rocks. Its form is that of a screw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

